line_1: Whose power the ample universe surrounds!
line_2: All-gracious God! whose goodness knows no bounds!

line_1: The Hoop secures, whatever it surrounds.
line_2: Fearless the Petticoat contemns his Frowns:

line_1: His sable sons with nearer course surrounds,
line_2: To either pole and life's remotest bounds.

line_1: No circling Gold his royal brow surrounds,
line_2: A Yard of Room his sphere of Action bounds;
And thou, my grot! whose lonely bounds
Where the half-cirque, which vision bounds,

line_1: But not till first a fencing hedge surrounds
line_2: Their future fields, and the enclosure bounds;
